        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 8:27PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 826 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Winnfield to 15 miles northeast of Colfax
to 9 miles north of Timber Trails to near Boyce to near Lacamp.
Movement was northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nebo, Urania, Vixen, Bosco, Rogers, Winnfield, Riverton, Standard,
Dry Prong, Joyce, Burlington, Clarks, Olla, Pollock, Midway, Grayson,
Williana, Georgetown, Sikes, and Spaulding.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for north
central Louisiana.</instruction>
